<br>
This annoyance was pointed out when I was camping the Drachnid Queen at Level 53 trying to get my Pally a Messenger of the Queen.<br>
<br>
A lesser Drachnid spawned and managed to land Deadly Velium Poison on me. My pet took care of the mob, but my health went down fast.<br>
<br>
I cast Phantom Armour on myself (+5 Regen) and meditated. the poison wore off, but I was very VERY low on health. Then one of those awful crystal crawlers, DEEP green to me, jumped me. Melees for about 26 max. I could get off the odd nuke while it was getting beat on by my pet, but the second spider who jumped me managed to kill me.<br>
<br>
Now I KNOW I did a lot wrong here<br>
<br>
I should have cast Phantom Armour right away and began using Bind Wounds on myself straight away, but I didn't. I didn't even consider it. While being beaty on, I should have cast Gate to escape, but I didn't.<br>
<br>
Aside from learninr from this annoying experience, I can't do a whole lot...<br>
<br>
But I've began thinking about a pure caster only self-heal. Since Mages lack damage absorbtion, we are even more vulnerable to geting meleed to death. I'm pretty sure if I had a 300hp rune up instead of my regen armour, I would have survived.<br>
<br>
So of the 3 classes who don't have heals (excluding PURE melees), Magicians are the most prone to this weakness.<br>
<br>
Wouldn't it be a novel idea to have a self only heal spell? I'm not talking vast quantities of HP or Cleric style efficiency.<br>
<br>
Just a Level 51 spell<br>
<br>
Refreshment of the Body<br>
Level 51<br>
Manna 200<br>
Heals 300 HP<br>
<br>
Hey, if that's still overpowering, let's give it a reagent cost... How about a Pearl? Those seem to be En Vogue with us right now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In fact, I wouldn't mind a 1:1 ration of health to manna.... Or hey, let's go crazy... 300 manna for a 200 hp heal! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This is only a spell I'd use in an emergency anyway, so I don't care about efficiency, I don't like getting hit anyway <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
